From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000002 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: YOUR NAME <your@email>
Date: Mon, 21 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] drm/panel: samsung-sofef00: move DCS init to enable()

The sofef00_panel_on() function sends DCS commands (exit sleep, set tear,
display on) from within prepare(). On the SM8150 (Snapdragon 855) DSI
pipeline, prepare() is called before the DSI PHY PLL has locked. Sending
DCS commands at that point causes mipi_dsi_dcs_write() to return -EINVAL,
which makes panel probe fail with:

  sofef00 panel: Failed to initialize panel: -22

Fix this by introducing a separate enable() callback that contains all
DCS initialisation. prepare() now only enables the regulator and asserts
the reset GPIO sequence, which is correct at the pre-PLL stage.
enable() is called after the bridge (and therefore the PHY PLL) is up.

Tested on Xiaomi Mi 9 (cepheus, SM8150) with the Samsung EA8076
(s6e3fc2x01) AMOLED panel.

Signed-off-by: YOUR NAME <your@email>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/panel/panel-samsung-sofef00.c | 22 +++++++++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 19 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/panel/panel-samsung-sofef00.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/panel/panel-samsung-sofef00.c
index 04ce925b3..212fb14ab 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/panel/panel-samsung-sofef00.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/panel/panel-samsung-sofef00.c
@@ -120,10 +120,19 @@ static int sofef00_panel_prepare(struct drm_panel *panel)

 	sofef00_panel_reset(ctx);

+	return 0;
+}
+
+static int sofef00_panel_enable(struct drm_panel *panel)
+{
+	struct sofef00_panel *ctx = to_sofef00_panel(panel);
+	struct device *dev = &ctx->dsi->dev;
+	int ret;
+
 	ret = sofef00_panel_on(ctx);
 	if (ret < 0) {
 		dev_err(dev, "Failed to initialize panel: %d\n", ret);
-		gpiod_set_value_cansleep(ctx->reset_gpio, 1);
 		return ret;
 	}

@@ -194,6 +203,7 @@ static int sofef00_panel_get_modes(struct drm_panel *panel, struct drm_connector

 static const struct drm_panel_funcs sofef00_panel_panel_funcs = {
 	.prepare = sofef00_panel_prepare,
+	.enable = sofef00_panel_enable,
 	.unprepare = sofef00_panel_unprepare,
 	.get_modes = sofef00_panel_get_modes,
 };
